<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-06-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-06-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="363" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d363">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Taylor</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-06-11"><hi rend="italic">June 11,
                                1895</hi>.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Instructions in Mora case mailed 6th instant with copy joint resolution
                            of Congress requesting President to insist upon payment of stipulated
                            indemnity, principal and interest. These instructions direct you, in
                            event that Spain is unable to pay the full amount at once, to urge an
                            immediate payment on account, end that arrangements be made for early
                            payment of balance.</p>
                        <p>See minister of foreign affairs and represent importance of satisfying
                            this claim irrespective of action on proposed claims convention. Press
                            for settlement and report by cable after receipt of said
                            instructions.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Olney.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>